<table width="50%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4">
	<tr>
		<td>
		<table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" align="center" class="boxtable">
			<tr>
				<td height="20" class="head" align="center" colspan="2">Support Logic - Post-Installation</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17" colspan="2"><b>Please read the following carefully - it contains important information about steps you should take in order to prevent your data from being compromised and to prevent error messages within the helpdesk!</b></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17"><i>You are strongly recommended to carry out the following two actions</i>:</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">1. <b>Delete this install.php file!!!</b></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">2. <b>Delete the update*.php files, unless you need to upgrade the helpdesk!!!</b></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">3. <b>Chmod config.php back to 644!!!</b></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17"><i>By following the next few steps, the helpdesk will be set up for use:</i></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">1. Login to admin.php</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">2. Create at least 2 staff members (you will see errors if you only create 1)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">3. Create a user (not essential, but useful to test the user part of the script)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">4. Change the preset categories</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">5. Change the preset priorities</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">6. Change the preset email messages</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">7. Send some test user tickets and staff replies to get acquainted with the system</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td height="17">8. Use your new helpdesk with your clients!</td>
			</tr>
			</table>
